Male terminalia (
Figs 19–24
). In lateral view, pygofer (
Fig. 20
) dorsal margin longer than ventral margin, dorsal margin slightly convex at anterior 1/3 then gently concave at posterior 2/3, ventral margin almost straight, posterior margin largely curved at dorsal 1/3, convex in the middle and finishing like a process ventrally, posterodorsal angle nearly acute. Subgenital plate, on ventral view (
Fig. 24
) almost parallel on 2/3 of their length then converging and crossing each other, apex pointed; in lateral view (
Fig. 21
), subgenital plate regularly tapering towards apex, curving dorsally then slightly ventrally at apex, covered with hairs on ventral half from basal to apical area; lateral plate roughly ovoid with anteroventral part narrower than posterodorsal one. Paramere, in lateral view (
Fig. 22
) dorsal margin largely concave subapically, slightly angular in middle and ventral margin straight subapically and rounded in middle, posterodorsal angle rounded without spine-like process, set of very short and scarce setae located on angular dorsal margin and rounded ventral margin. Aedeagus (
Fig. 23
) with apical extension sharp in apex curling towards ventral direction, posterior protrusion hook-shaped.
